Adjust rack to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Trim and quarter @zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into 1-inch-thick pieces. Core, deseed, and dice @bell pepper{1} into 1-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and slice @shallot{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Toss zucchini, bell pepper, and shallot on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp}, @Tunisian spice blend{1%tbsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{18-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, slice each @whole wheat pita{2} into 6 triangles; rub all over with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} until evenly coated. Spread out on a second baking sheet. Sprinkle on both sides with @salt{} and @garlic powder{1/2%tsp} (all for 4 servings). Bake on middle rack until crisp and browned at edges, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and cook until slightly softened, ~{1%minute}. Add ¾ cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then stir in @couscous{1/2%cup}. Immediately cover and remove pot from heat; let sit until ready to serve.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @yogurt{2%oz}, @sour cream{4%tbsp}, @feta cheese{1/2%cup}, a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, and a squeeze of lemon juice to taste. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fluff couscous with a #fork{}; stir in lemon zest and season with salt and pepper. Divide between plates; top with roasted veggies and sauce. Sprinkle with scallion greens. Serve with pita chips and any remaining lemon wedges on the side.